Imagine losing a father to cancer then two years down the line, the mother falls ill and spends a whole year in the intensive care unit then also passes on. the bill, a whopping 20 million shillings. such has been the story of a Nairobi family that has been forced to surrender their family home and rent a cheaper house as they struggle to raise the amount with the body of their mother detained in the morgue for three months now. KTN's mark namaswa has the family's plight.